main event: A military pilot and ground radar reported seeing an object similar to an F-86 fighter aircraft approach at a high rate of speed, without any sound, in the vicinity of Sacramento, California on 7/11/1955.
interesting points: The object was observed through both ground radar and air-visual means.
The sighting only lasted for one minute.
The Director of Intelligence of the 25th ADIv. attributed the sighting to a failed weather balloon released from Beales AFB in that area.
The conclusion was that the object was likely a weather balloon.
The report includes both visual and radar data, but the object's characteristics do not match a typical weather balloon.
sighted object: an object similar to an F-86 fighter aircraft
